Majlis Podcast The Fallout From Detaining A Kyrgyz Opposition Leader

The detention of Omurbek Tekebaev the leader of Kyrgyzstans AtaMeken party has provided opponents of President Almazbek Atambaev and his Social Democratic Party of Kyrgyzstan SDPK with a fresh rallying point

The countrys presidential election is scheduled for November and Atambaev is constitutionally prohibited from running so this promises to be the most contested presidential election in Kyrgyzstans 25year history

That makes Tekebaevs detention not only a political

Detained Kyrgyz Opposition Party Leader Tekebaev Named As Presidential Candidate

Kyrgyzstans opposition AtaMeken Fatherland party has named its detained leader Omurbek Tekebaev as the party‚Äôs candidate for the November presidential election

The decision was made at an extraordinary AtaMeken congress held in the capital Bishkek on March 5

Tekebaev a former parliament speaker

Omurbek Tekebaev Political Pugilist At Center Of Kyrgyzstans Storm

The detention on arrival in Bishkek of Omurbek Tekebaev a veteran politician and leader of the AtaMeken party immediately set off political friction in Kyrgyzstan

Modest protests started the same day and continued on February 27 when a court ordered Tekebaev held for two months while he is investigated on charges of fraud and corruption The demonstrations continue
